    		<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>School Closing Notice</strong></h1>
<h2>UPDATE— April 17, 2020</h2>
<h3></h3>
<p>Dear Bulldog Family,</p>
<p>I’m sure that most of you are aware that Gov. Abbot has closed all schools in Texas for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.  I am deeply saddened that this has happened, but in order to get through this pandemic, I understand.  This is really a sad and unfortunate situation for all of our students, parents, teachers, and staff, but more especially for our seniors.</p>
<p>Seniors, I am especially sorry for each of you and cannot imagine this happening to me as a senior in my spring semester before graduation.  I know that you are missing out on some of your most memorable moments right now, and if I could change this for you guys I would.  I miss interacting with each of you every day and it breaks my heart that I will not get to spend any more time with you as students at Centerville ISD.  I just ask you to keep your heads up and keep pressing forward.  I know that each of you will do big things in life and I look forward to watching you all grow and become great people within our community.  We will have graduation!!!  I don’t know when or how it will play out, but it will happen for you guys.  We will also do our best to have an athletic banquet and FFA banquet to honor what you guys have accomplished.  Again, I can’t tell you what this will look like, or when it will happen, but we will provide these for you.  I just want you to know that I genuinely care about each of you and know that we are here for you.</p>
<p>Centerville ISD will continue to provide lunches each day and will also continue providing online resources and packets to all of our students. We will be updating with more information as it becomes available this coming week.  Please be patient as we work our ways through these uncertain and ever changing times. The Texas Education Agency is currently working on plans and details to help us navigate through this situation.  Meanwhile, we ask each parent and student to continue the hard work that you all have been doing and we will get through this.  I miss the entire <strong>Bulldog Family</strong> and I cannot wait to get back together.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Mark Brown<br>
Superintendent<br>
Centerville ISD</p>
